    <stitle>BE 200 BUS FRONT END AND BODY COMPONENTS - ADJUSTMENTS - HEADLIGHT ADJUSTMENT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
        <title>HEADLIGHT ADJUSTMENT</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>Do not replace or handle halogen headlight bulbs while hot. Property damage and/or personal injury
                    may occur. Allow bulb and/or sockets to cool sufficiently before handling.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <important>
                <para>When changing halogen headlight bulbs, follow manufacturer's instructions for proper handling of
                    subject bulbs. Not following manufacturer's instructions may cause premature failure of headlight
                    bulb.
                </para>
            </important>
        </specpara>
        <para>To adjust the headlight direction, release hood latch and tilt hood forward.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate adjustment control stem on rear of headlight housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f47006309">Figure 309, Item 2</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Rotate the adjustment screw clockwise or counter clockwise to adjust the height of the
                headlight beam.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f47006309" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g47006309.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 309. Headlight Adjustment</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. HEADLIGHT HARNESS</callout1>
                <callout1>2. ADJUSTMENT SCREW</callout1>
                <callout1>3. BULB / SOCKET COVER</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
